‘Independence Day,’ followed by ‘#EndSARS,’ emerged the top trending search terms on Google in Nigeria over the past 30 days, the internet tech giant has disclosed.
 
According to a statement by Google yesterday, state election results were also among the top trending Google searches in Nigeria this month.
 
It added that the top searches were also linked to the most asked questions, which concerned a leading activist, Aisha Yesufu, the whereabouts of the President, Muhammadu Buhari, and the winner of Big Brother Nigeria.
 
October 1 marked Nigeria’s 60th anniversary of its independence from Great Britain, but the celebration turned into a series of protests across the country’s major cities as people expressed their anger over corruption and increase to petrol price and electricity tariff.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .